hpnicfDot11STATION.name: hpnicfDot11STATION

revisions.description: Add new node hpnicfDot11StationUpTimeTicks, hpnicfDot11StationSecIEStatus to hpnicfDot11StationAssociateTable.
Add new node hpnicfDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt and hpnicfDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt to hpnicfDot11StationStatisTable
Modified to add new trap and add hpnicfDot11StationRxNoise to hpnicfDot11StationAssociateTable.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfDot11STATION.description: This MIB defines the configuration and statistic information of stations. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Control And Provisioning of Wireless Access Points Protocol The short name of protocol is CAPWAP. AC will control and manage AP by CAPWAP tunnel protocol defined by IETF. Also, a data tunnel will be set up between AC and AP. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associated with the AP. station (Client Station) A wireless device in a wireless network associated with an access point. MIC Message Integrity Check. A MIC can, optionally, be added to WEP-encrypted 802.11 frames. SSID Radio Service Set ID. It is used for identification during association. STA (WSTA) A non-AP 802.11 wireless station. WEP Wired Equivalent Privacy. 'WEP' is generally used to refer to 802.11 encryption. RSSI It is the received signal strength indication. It suggests the quality of received signal. RTS Request to Send, it is used to gain control of the medium for the transmission of 'large' frames, in which 'large' is defined by the RTS threshold in the network card driver. CTS Clear to Send, it is used to answer RTS frames. AKM The authentication and key management method defined by 802.11i, and which includes 802.1x and pre-shared key.

hpnicfDot11StationAssociateTable.name: hpnicfDot11StationAssociateTable
hpnicfDot11StationAssociateTable.description: This table contains the information of stations which are associating with the wireless network (current AC).

hpnicfDot11StationAssociateEntry.name: hpnicfDot11StationAssociateEntry
hpnicfDot11StationAssociateEntry.description: Each entry contains association information of each station.

hpnicfDot11StationMAC.name: hpnicfDot11StationMAC
hpnicfDot11StationMAC.description: Represents the unique MAC Address of station.

hpnicfDot11StationIPAddress.name: hpnicfDot11StationIPAddress
hpnicfDot11StationIPAddress.description: Represents the IP address of the station.

hpnicfDot11StationUserName.name: hpnicfDot11StationUserName
hpnicfDot11StationUserName.description: Represents the user name of the station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxRateSet.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxRateSet
hpnicfDot11StationTxRateSet.description: Represents the current transmit data rates for this station. Each byte will represent one rate. If the MSB(Most significant bit) is set, then this rate is a mandantory rate. Otherwise, it is optional.

hpnicfDot11StationUpTime.name: hpnicfDot11StationUpTime
hpnicfDot11StationUpTime.description: The time in seconds, how long this station has been associated with this device.

hpnicfDot11StationSignalStrength.name: hpnicfDot11StationSignalStrength
hpnicfDot11StationSignalStrength.description: Represents a device-dependent measure of the signal strength of latest packet received from this station.

hpnicfDot11StationRSSI.name: hpnicfDot11StationRSSI
hpnicfDot11StationRSSI.description: Represents a device-dependent measure of the RSSI. It is the received signal strength indication. The maximum value is defined by chip set vendors

hpnicfDot11StationChannel.name: hpnicfDot11StationChannel
hpnicfDot11StationChannel.description: Represents current radio channel used by station.

hpnicfDot11StationPowerSaveMode.name: hpnicfDot11StationPowerSaveMode
hpnicfDot11StationPowerSaveMode.description: Represents the power management mode of this station. The following values are supported: active - This station is not in power-save mode and it is actively sending or receiving data. powersave - This station is in power-save mode and it wakes up after sometime to check for buffer data.

hpnicfDot11StationAid.name: hpnicfDot11StationAid
hpnicfDot11StationAid.description: Represents the association identification number of station.

hpnicfDot11StationVlanId.name: hpnicfDot11StationVlanId
hpnicfDot11StationVlanId.description: Represents Vlan ID to which the station is associated.

hpnicfDot11StationAuthenMode.name: hpnicfDot11StationAuthenMode
hpnicfDot11StationAuthenMode.description: Represents the Authentication mode defined by 802.11.

hpnicfDot11StationAKMMode.name: hpnicfDot11StationAKMMode
hpnicfDot11StationAKMMode.description: Represents the key management mode defined by 802.11i.

hpnicfDot11StationSecurityCiphers.name: hpnicfDot11StationSecurityCiphers
hpnicfDot11StationSecurityCiphers.description: Represents the frame encryption cipher type used by station.

hpnicfDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode.name: hpnicfDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode
hpnicfDot11StationSSIDEncryptMode.description: Represents the encryption mode for this ESS.

hpnicfDot11StationRxSNR.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxSNR
hpnicfDot11StationRxSNR.description: Represents the signal and noise strength ratio of frame reception.

hpnicfDot11StationTxRate.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxRate
hpnicfDot11StationTxRate.description: Represents the transmission rate of frame.

hpnicfDot11StationRxRate.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxRate
hpnicfDot11StationRxRate.description: Represents the reception rate of frame.

hpnicfDot11StationVendorName.name: hpnicfDot11StationVendorName
hpnicfDot11StationVendorName.description: Represents the vendor name of the station.

hpnicfDot11StationRadioMode.name: hpnicfDot11StationRadioMode
hpnicfDot11StationRadioMode.description: Represents which radio type supported by the station. The WLAN system support the following possible radio types. dot11a(1), dot11b(2), dot11g(4), dot11n(8) For a station,it could support only one radio type at the same time.

hpnicfDot11StationRxNoise.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxNoise
hpnicfDot11StationRxNoise.description: Represents the received noise of the station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxSpeed.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxSpeed
hpnicfDot11StationTxSpeed.description: Represents the bytes of transmitted data frames to the station per second in sample interval.

hpnicfDot11StationRxSpeed.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxSpeed
hpnicfDot11StationRxSpeed.description: Represents the bytes of received data frames from the station per second in sample interval.

hpnicfDot11StationWmmMode.name: hpnicfDot11StationWmmMode
hpnicfDot11StationWmmMode.description: Represents the QoS mode of station. The following values are supported: wmm - This QoS function is supported by this station. nonwmm - This QoS function is not supported by this station.

hpnicfDot11StationSecIEStatus.name: hpnicfDot11StationSecIEStatus
hpnicfDot11StationSecIEStatus.description: Represents the security Information element for this station.

hpnicfDot11StationUpTimeTicks.name: hpnicfDot11StationUpTimeTicks
hpnicfDot11StationUpTimeTicks.description: Represents how long this station has been associated with this device.

hpnicfDot11StationRadioMode2.name: hpnicfDot11StationRadioMode2
hpnicfDot11StationRadioMode2.description: Represents which radio type supported by the station. The WLAN system support the following possible radio types. dot11a(1), dot11b(2), dot11g(4), dot11an(8), dot11gn(16) For a station,it could support only one radio type at the same time.

hpnicfDot11StationAssTime.name: hpnicfDot11StationAssTime
hpnicfDot11StationAssTime.description: Represents the time at which the station connected.

hpnicfDot11StationUserAuthType.name: hpnicfDot11StationUserAuthType
hpnicfDot11StationUserAuthType.description: Represents the type of user authentication with this station. portalAuth - The authentication lunched by portal pop-up program which is need input username and passward,exclude MAC authentication. authFree - There is no need others authentiaction,user will surf internet after association. associateAuth - Include WEP PSK 802.1X authentication. macAuth - MAC Authentication apply with access device, a Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service (RADIUS) server or message netgate to realize fast authentication.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTest.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTest
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTest.description: This object is used to start rfping test of the station. It will return false for get operation.

hpnicfDot11StationMaxRate.name: hpnicfDot11StationMaxRate
hpnicfDot11StationMaxRate.description: Represents the max negotiation rate of the station.

hpnicfDot11StationPowerSaveModeCM.name: hpnicfDot11StationPowerSaveModeCM
hpnicfDot11StationPowerSaveModeCM.description: Represents the power management mode of the client. The following values are supported: active - This client is not in power-save mode and it is actively sending or receiving data. powersave - This client is in power-save mode and it wakes up after some time to check for buffer data.

hpnicfDot11StationAuthenModeCM.name: hpnicfDot11StationAuthenModeCM
hpnicfDot11StationAuthenModeCM.description: Represents the authentication mode defined by 802.11. The following values are supported: opensystem - Do not authenticate. sharedkey - System will use challenge message to authenticate the client.

hpnicfDot11StationAKMModeCM.name: hpnicfDot11StationAKMModeCM
hpnicfDot11StationAKMModeCM.description: Represents the key management mode defined by 802.11i. The following values are supported: none - no key management mode configured, psk - pre-shared key authentication, radius - 802.1x authentication, wlanex - wlanex.

hpnicfDot11StationSecurityCiphersCM.name: hpnicfDot11StationSecurityCiphersCM
hpnicfDot11StationSecurityCiphersCM.description: Represents the frame encryption cipher type used by station. The following values are supported: none - clear text or no cipher method is configure, wep40 - 40-bit WEP key, wep104 - 104-bit WEP key, tkip - WPA Temporal Key encryption, aesccmp - WPA AES CCMP encryption, wpisms4 - ext encryption.

hpnicfDot11StationSecIEStatusCM.name: hpnicfDot11StationSecIEStatusCM
hpnicfDot11StationSecIEStatusCM.description: Represents the security Information element for this station. The following values are supported: none - both wpa and wpa2 are disabled, wpa - only enable wpa, wpa2 - only enable wpa2, wlanex - only enable wlanex.

hpnicfDot11StationAPRelationTable.name: hpnicfDot11StationAPRelationTable
hpnicfDot11StationAPRelationTable.description: This table contains relation-ship between station, AP, Radio and WLANID, and the detailed information of station is kept in the hpnicfDot11StaAssociateTable table.

hpnicfDot11StationAPRelationEntry.name: hpnicfDot11StationAPRelationEntry
hpnicfDot11StationAPRelationEntry.description: Each entry contains relation-ship information with AP, Radio and WLANID of each station.

hpnicfDot11CurrAPID.name: hpnicfDot11CurrAPID
hpnicfDot11CurrAPID.description: To uniquely identify each AP, and relation-ship between hpnicfDot11CurrAPID and AP device will be static.

hpnicfDot11CurrWlanID.name: hpnicfDot11CurrWlanID
hpnicfDot11CurrWlanID.description: Represents WLAN ID of the BSS the station associated to.

hpnicfDot11CurrAntennaID.name: hpnicfDot11CurrAntennaID
hpnicfDot11CurrAntennaID.description: Represents Antenna ID of the station associated to.

hpnicfDot11StationStatisTable.name: hpnicfDot11StationStatisTable
hpnicfDot11StationStatisTable.description: This table contains statistics and status of all stations in the hpnicfDot11StaAssociateTable.

hpnicfDot11StationStatisEntry.name: hpnicfDot11StationStatisEntry
hpnicfDot11StationStatisEntry.description: This entry contains statistics and status for each station.

hpnicfDot11StationRxFrameCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxFrameCnt
hpnicfDot11StationRxFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are received by AP from station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxFrameCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxFrameCnt
hpnicfDot11StationTxFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are sent to station from AP.

hpnicfDot11StationDropFrameCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationDropFrameCnt
hpnicfDot11StationDropFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of frames that are dropped.

hpnicfDot11StationRxFrameBytes.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxFrameBytes
hpnicfDot11StationRxFrameBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are received by AP from station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxFrameBytes.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxFrameBytes
hpnicfDot11StationTxFrameBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are sent to station from AP.

hpnicfDot11StationDropFrameBytes.name: hpnicfDot11StationDropFrameBytes
hpnicfDot11StationDropFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes are dropped.

hpnicfDot11StationRxRetryPkts.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxRetryPkts
hpnicfDot11StationRxRetryPkts.description: Represents the count of frames that are retransmitted to AP from station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxRetryPkts.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxRetryPkts
hpnicfDot11StationTxRetryPkts.description: Represents the count of frames that are retransmitted to station from AP.

hpnicfDot11StationRxRetryBytes.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxRetryBytes
hpnicfDot11StationRxRetryBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are retransmitted to AP from station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxRetryBytes.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxRetryBytes
hpnicfDot11StationTxRetryBytes.description: Represents the count of bytes that are retransmitted to station from AP.

hpnicfDot11StationThroughput.name: hpnicfDot11StationThroughput
hpnicfDot11StationThroughput.description: Represents how many payload bytes of data frame are sent and received by station.

hpnicfDot11StationSuccessTxCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationSuccessTxCnt
hpnicfDot11StationSuccessTxCnt.description: Represents how many frames have been successfully sent to station.

hpnicfDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt
hpnicfDot11StationSuccessTxDataCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been successfully sent to station.

hpnicfDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt
hpnicfDot11StationRxDataFrameCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been received from station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt
hpnicfDot11StationTxDataFrameCnt.description: Represents how many data frames have been sent to station.

hpnicfDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes
hpnicfDot11StationRxDataFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes of data frames have been received from station.

hpnicfDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes.name: hpnicfDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes
hpnicfDot11StationTxDataFrameBytes.description: Represents how many bytes of data frames have been sent to station.

hpnicfDot11StationRxFragCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationRxFragCnt
hpnicfDot11StationRxFragCnt.description: Represents the number of fragmented data frames that received from station.

hpnicfDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt
hpnicfDot11StaRxErrDataFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of error data frames that are received by AP from station.

hpnicfDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt
hpnicfDot11StaTxRetryDataFrameCnt.description: Represents the count of data frames that are retransmitted to station from AP.

hpnicfDot11StaTxDataRatePkts.name: hpnicfDot11StaTxDataRatePkts
hpnicfDot11StaTxDataRatePkts.description: Represents how many data frames of each rate have been received from station.

hpnicfDot11StaRxDataRatePkts.name: hpnicfDot11StaRxDataRatePkts
hpnicfDot11StaRxDataRatePkts.description: Represents how many data frames of each rate have been sent to station.

hpnicfDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts.name: hpnicfDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts
hpnicfDot11StaTxSignalStrengthPkts.description: Represents how many data frames of different signal strength have been received from station.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTable.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTable
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTable.description: This table contains statistics of all stations in the hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTable.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingEntry.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingEntry
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingEntry.description: This entry contains statistics for each station's RfPing results.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingIndex.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingIndex
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingIndex.description: Represents the rate index for the station.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRate.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRate
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRate.description: Represents the rate at which the radio interface sends wireless ping frames.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTxCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTxCnt
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingTxCnt.description: Represents the number of wireless ping frames that the radio interface sent.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRxCnt.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRxCnt
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRxCnt.description: Represents the number of wireless ping frames that the radio interface received from the client.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRssi.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRssi
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRssi.description: Represents the client signal strength detected by the AP.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRetries.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRetries
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRetries.description: Represents the total number of retransmitted ping frames.

hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRtt.name: hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRtt
hpnicfDot11StationRfPingRtt.description: Round-trip time (RTT) from the time when the radio interface send a ping packet to the time when it receives a response from the client.

hpnicfDot11StationMICErrorTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationMICErrorTrap
hpnicfDot11StationMICErrorTrap.description: This notification is to indicate the occurrence of a MIC failure in a certain station.

hpnicfDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap
hpnicfDot11StationAuthenErrorTrap.description: This notification is to indicate which station happened authentication failure.

hpnicfDot11StationAuthorFailTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationAuthorFailTrap
hpnicfDot11StationAuthorFailTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station authorization fails.

hpnicfDot11StationAssocFailTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationAssocFailTrap
hpnicfDot11StationAssocFailTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station association fails.

hpnicfDot11StationDeAssocTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationDeAssocTrap
hpnicfDot11StationDeAssocTrap.description: This trap is sent if a station de-association occurred.

hpnicfDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap
hpnicfDot11StationAuthorSuccTrap.description: This trap is sent when a station is authorized successfully.

hpnicfDot11StationRoamingTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationRoamingTrap
hpnicfDot11StationRoamingTrap.description: This trap is sent when a station roamed successfully.

hpnicfDot11StationDisconnectTrap.name: hpnicfDot11StationDisconnectTrap
hpnicfDot11StationDisconnectTrap.description: This notification is sent when station disconnects with AP.

hpnicfDot11UserDisconnectTrap.name: hpnicfDot11UserDisconnectTrap
hpnicfDot11UserDisconnectTrap.description: This notification is sent when user disconnects with AP.

hpnicfDot11StationTrapBSSID.name: hpnicfDot11StationTrapBSSID
hpnicfDot11StationTrapBSSID.description: Represents on which BSSID of AP the event happened.

hpnicfDot11StationTrapStaMAC.name: hpnicfDot11StationTrapStaMAC
hpnicfDot11StationTrapStaMAC.description: Represents the MAC address of station which happened message integrity check (MIC) errors.

hpnicfDot11StationSessionStartTime.name: hpnicfDot11StationSessionStartTime
hpnicfDot11StationSessionStartTime.description: Represents the time at which the station connected.

hpnicfDot11StationAssocFailCause.name: hpnicfDot11StationAssocFailCause
hpnicfDot11StationAssocFailCause.description: Represents the cause of the station association failure.

hpnicfDot11StationAuthorFailCause.name: hpnicfDot11StationAuthorFailCause
hpnicfDot11StationAuthorFailCause.description: Represents the cause of the station authorization failure.

hpnicfDot11StationFailCauseDesc.name: hpnicfDot11StationFailCauseDesc
hpnicfDot11StationFailCauseDesc.description: Represents the failure description of the station.

hpnicfDot11StationSessionDuration.name: hpnicfDot11StationSessionDuration
hpnicfDot11StationSessionDuration.description: Represents the duration of the station sesssion.

hpnicfDot11StationRoamingTime.name: hpnicfDot11StationRoamingTime
hpnicfDot11StationRoamingTime.description: Represents the time at which the station roamed.

hpnicfDot11StationACIPAddress.name: hpnicfDot11StationACIPAddress
hpnicfDot11StationACIPAddress.description: For roam-in station, it represents the ip address of home AC. For roam-out station, it represents the ip address of foreign AC.

hpnicfDot11StationAPName.name: hpnicfDot11StationAPName
hpnicfDot11StationAPName.description: Name of the AP which the station connects to.

hpnicfDot11StationBSSID.name: hpnicfDot11StationBSSID
hpnicfDot11StationBSSID.description: BSSID which the station connects to.

hpnicfDot11StaDisconnectReason.name: hpnicfDot11StaDisconnectReason
hpnicfDot11StaDisconnectReason.description: Reason why the station disconnects with the AP.

hpnicfDot11StationACIPv6Add.name: hpnicfDot11StationACIPv6Add
hpnicfDot11StationACIPv6Add.description: For roam-in station, it represents the IPv6 address of home AC. For roam-out station, it represents the IPv6 address of foreign AC.

hpnicfDot11StationTrapAPMacAddress.name: hpnicfDot11StationTrapAPMacAddress
hpnicfDot11StationTrapAPMacAddress.description: Represents the MAC address of an AP.
